President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Jerome H. (Jay) Powell and Jeremy C. Stein to the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System. Powell is a visiting scholar at the Bipartisan Policy Center and previously served as Undersecretary of the Treasury for Finance under President George H.W. Bush. He also has experience in the private sector, having worked as a partner at The Carlyle Group. Powell is currently involved in various charitable and educational institutions. Stein is a professor of economics at Harvard University and has previously taught at M.I.T.'s Sloan School of Management and the Harvard Business School. His research has covered various topics in finance and he has served in the Obama Administration as a senior advisor to the Treasury Secretary. Both nominees have impressive backgrounds and knowledge of economic and monetary policy.